The Giver Unfolded

Chapter 1 Analysis

Project Introduction

14% of adults in the United States are functionally illiterate. Functionally illiterate is defined as reading below the 4th grade reading level. Many adults enroll in literacy tutoring programs that assist them with increasing their reading level to either, 1) complete their GED, 2) enroll in college or enter the workforce, 3) assist their children at home, or 4) other personal learning goals. These agencies are not equip with adult reading materials purely because they dont exist. Instead, agencies provide their tutors with childrens books that are complementary to their adult learners reading level. Children books are not topically engaging or relevant to most adult learners. I examine the parts of speech found within The Giver - a book found in most 8th grade curriculum across the country - to help conceptualize what concepts should be taught at the 8th grade level. This project is the beginning of a large-scale examination of 4th through 8th grade books to assist with creating a formula to be used in establishing adult reading materials.
